1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,730
and do other work that requires top mental performance.

2
00:00:04,240 --> 00:00:09,490
Rather than wait for the spirit to move you, sit down and move your spirit.

3
00:00:10,559 --> 00:00:13,890
Here's a special technique guaranteed to help you.

4
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:16,049
Use a pencil and paper.

5
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:20,930
A simple pencil is the greatest concentration tool money can buy.

6
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:29,410
If I had to choose between an ultra-fancy, deeply carpeted, beautifully decorated soundproof office and a pencil and paper,

7
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:32,290
I'd choose the pencil and paper every time.

8
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:36,770
With a pencil and paper, you can tie your mind to a problem.

9
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:43,410
When you write a thought on paper, your full attention is automatically focused on that thought.

10
00:00:43,760 --> 00:00:49,650
That's because the mind is not designed to think one thought and write another at the same time.

11
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:54,210
When you write on paper, you write on your mind, too.

12
00:00:54,640 --> 00:01:02,770
Tests prove conclusively that you remember something much longer and much more exactly if you write the thought on paper.

13
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:11,490
And once you master the pencil and paper technique for concentration, you can think in noisy or other distracting situations.

14
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:16,290
When you want to think, start writing or doodling or diagramming.
